If you need to vary the item number for e.g. different questions, you&#39;d need to have the question number as a prop or as part of your state, then do this:


    const questionIndex = this.state.index;

    const currentItem = this.state.data[questionIndex];
    return (
        &lt;FlatList
            data={[currentItem]}
            keyExtractor={(x, i) =&gt; i}
            renderItem={({item}) =&gt;  &lt;Text&gt;{item.id}&lt;/Text&gt;}
          /&gt;
     ) 

Though as others have pointed out, a FlatList is intended to be used for a list of items, so if you only need to show a single item you don&#39;t need it:

    const {data, index} = this.state
